<HEAD>Idaho Guard Members Reported Missing When Helicopter Fails To Return</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOISE, Idaho (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four Idaho National Guard crew members were
reported missing Saturday after their helicopter failed to return
from a routine training flight.
   The crew left Gowen Field, adjacent to Boise Municipal Airport,
at about 5 p.m. Saturday and were due to return by 6:30 p.m., said
1st Lt. Michael Gollaher, Gowen Field deputy public affairs officer.
