<HEAD>Typhoon Kills Eight in the Philippines</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Recasts first two grafs to delete redundancy. Pick up 3rd pvs,
``Civil Defense...'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Typhoon Sarah caused flooding and
landslides in the northern Philippines that left eight people dead,
nine missing and more than 1,000 families homeless, officials said
Sunday.
   By midday, the storm was centered 50 miles southeast of Basco
town at the northern tip of the Philippines and was headed toward
southern Taiwan, the weather bureau said. Sarah, with top winds of
72 mph, produced heavy rain.
   Civil Defense and Red Cross officials, who provided the damage
report, said two children drowned Saturday in Ilocos Sur province
after their house was swept away by floodwaters. An unidentified man
also drowned in the province.
   In the mountain province of Benguet, landslides killed five
people in Banagan village, the officials said.
   Landslides cut off all roads leading to the northern resort city
of Baguio for several hours but were cleared Sunday, rescue
officials said.
