<HEAD>Missing Girl Found Unharmed After Night in Bus</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A missing 5-year-old girl spent the
night in a locked school bus after she apparently got on the wrong
bus and didn't know when to get off.
   Kathy Chao was tired and hungry, but otherwise unharmed, when
found Saturday, 22 hours after she disappeared, according to police
Detective Joe Sledge.
   Kathy, who speaks Laotian and very little English, told her
parents she sat far in back of the bus and waited for the driver to
call her name. But he never did.
   ``She said she looked everywhere for her bus stop, but she didn't
see it,'' said her father, Kao Nai Saechao. ``She said she was
afraid to get off.''
   The girl was found by two men who heard her crying inside a
fenced bus yard after she jumped off the bus through a rear
emergency door, said one of the men, contractor Chris Neary.
   Kathy's family celebrated her return Saturday with a Taoist
religious feast.
