<HEAD>Three Die Inside Well</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANDY HOOK, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A young man died in a well, along with a
brother and sister-in-law who tried to rescue him, when they were
apparently overcome by gas fumes, a coroner said.
   Kenneth Cox, about 24; his 27-year-old brother, Curtis; and
Curtis Cox's wife, Jamie Lee, 25, died Saturday while trying to
clean out an open well 15 to 20 miles northwest of this northeastern
Kentucky town, Elliott County Coroner Carl Eldridge said.
   The three had just detonated an explosive inside the 2-foot-wide,
12-foot-deep well when Kenneth Cox apparently fell in, Eldridge said.
   ``His brother Curtis went in to assist him and both were
apparently overcome with some noxious fumes _ some type of gas,
possibly methane,'' Eldridge said. ``Then Jamie went in to assist
them and was overcome ...''
   Family members found the three in the well, Eldridge said. He
said tests were being done to determine what kind of gas was in the
well.
