<HEAD>Apartment Fire Kills Father, Sons</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CEDAR MILL, Ore. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A father and two sons died early Sunday
when their apartment was engulfed by fire in this suburb northwest
of Portland, a fire official said. Three other family members
escaped.
   The bodies of Roy Hopkins, 30, and his sons Brian, 8, and Jason,
7, were found huddled together in one of the apartment's two
bedrooms, said Tualatin Valley Fire and Fire and Rescue spokesman
Jim Washburn.
   A third son, 4-year-old Thomas; Roy Hopkins' mother, Lois
Elizabeth McCullagh, 53; and her 56-year-old husband, John, escaped
through a ground-floor bedroom window. Lois McCullagh was in fair
condition at St. Vincent Hospital and Medical Center, where she was
being treated for smoke inhalation and a broken ankle.
   ``If they had gone through the apartment, rather than out the
window, I think we'd be looking at six people dead, rather than just
three,'' said Washburn.
   Noise from the fire, which broke out around 5:30 a.m., woke up
John McCullagh, Washburn said. McCullagh forced his wife and
grandson out the window, then climbed out after them.
   The cause of the fire was not known.
